Program: Outlook
Title: The making of a disco star
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csz38m
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 2 Feb 2020
Sequins, spandex and Rasputin? Dust off your gold spandex for a dive into the world of 1970s disco. Marcia Barrett, a lead singer of the chart-conquering Boney M, discusses her life with the band - including getting mobbed behind the iron curtain. This episode was first broadcast on 18 August, 2018. Presenter: Emily Webb Producer: Maryam Maruf and Katy Davis Image: Boney M's Marcia Barrett performing on stage, September 1979 Credit: Getty Images Show less